comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/anmm_thecommons] Wonderful - how useful to have a "learned observer"! I am going to vote for 1898, because in 1899 the KÖNIGIN LUISE was "moored off Neutral Bay" instead of previous years' courses near Lavender Bay. This photo looks like it is nearer Lavender Bay. 1898 Anniversary Day Regatta report - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14160588 1899 Anniversary Day Regatta report - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14197303
